{
  "stem": "11000.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You woke up and-- realizing where you are, what you have to face again, and you reach the stage where you start thinking about probably better off not being there and face all this again.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the suicide rate was-- was pretty high, and it was easy to do because the camp was surrounded with high-voltage wire, and all you had to do is go and touch the wire.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And of course, the first thing every morning, you saw that they had a special commando of prisoners who had that cart, and they used to go out the camp first and pick up all the bodies that were lying there of prisoners who went there during the night.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To escape, I think from my experience, was an impossibility in those camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] First of all, even if you would get out of the camp, where would you go to?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, here you are, looking almost like a skeleton with a striped suit in a country where you can't speak the language.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And don't forget, there were days where Germany were-- was winning the war, and people were not too unfriendly against the German regime because they benefited a lot by what they did to us.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember when-- the short distance that we had to march from the camp to the factory.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Germany was winning the war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People stood there and-- what they yelled at us, and the children were allowed to kick us and throw stones at us, and-- and-- and you felt like, you know, you weren't human anymore.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You're a part of the-- you were treated like an animal.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I think I learned that-- that killing a human being really isn't the biggest crime.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
